Reflection

The wines data set contains information on 1599 wines across twelve variables from around 2009. Being an example dataset I expected clear relations between its features, however barely you can find some relations. First thing surprised me was that most of wines measured had a quality of 5 or 6 while qualities as 3, 4 or 8 have very few samples. I guess it means that most of wines has a normal quality and just a few have a high or low quality.

The most cleare relations I saw was the alcohol concentration, it is related with quality and with density.

Another thing is every feature has a perfect value indicidually, as you can see in the firsts graphs where I compare quality with every feature. However, when you have a best quality wine, these values change. It is like a lower value in alcohol can compensate a higher value in sugar.
